The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Saturday, February 21, 2004 				 Shourie sorry for I-word
																								New Delhi, Feb. 20 (PTI): Disinvestment minister Arun Shourie today stood by his criticism of the methodology and inference of the Comptroller and Auditor Generals observations on the privatisation of Centaur Hotel which was completed a year ago but said he was sorry for using the term idiotic.																								I am unreservedly sorry for the word idiotic... The methodology for determining the notional losses was peculiar... I stand by my critique of the methodology and inference of the CAG report, Shourie said. He maintained that the relationship between his ministry and the statutory auditor was most cordial and the two had held workshops together.																								The minister was commenting on the controversy triggered by a CAG report on the sale of Centaur Hotel Mumbai to Batra Hospitality.																								Shourie said he would meet comptroller and auditor general V.. Kaul on Monday after his return from the Northeast to explain all the facts about the deal. 
